Juggling Throw	CATEGORY:Special Ability	SOURCEPAGE:p.83	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	KEY:Juggling Throw ~ Arcane Juggler		DEFINE:JugglingThrowBonus|0	DESC: Using this ability, the arcane juggler can throw a number of items per round equal to his number of attacks per round as long as they are being used in a juggle. Throwing items from a juggle is considered a standard action, but the arcane juggler is able to do it without incurring the normal -4 penalty for throwing objects that are normally not meant to be thrown, for example a pot. At higher levels the arcane juggler gains a bonus to his attack rolls when throwing items from the arcane juggle only. The bonus is as indicated in the column and it is not cumulative. Doing so does not provoke an attack of opportunity, and no strength bonuses apply to thrown items from a juggle.
