	SOURCEPAGE:p.145		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.SpellLike		KEY:Forbidden ~ Wyrm Master
Forbidden: Wyrm masters are forbidden from knowingly touching items such as potions and wands designed for dragon control, as well as weapons that are specifically designed to harm dragons. Additionally, a wyrm master cannot deliberately injure a dragon unless the dragon has gone rogue and threatens other dragons, or has willingly and without any reason killed loyal followers of Alfheim-Rigel. Even in such extreme situations, he must first attempt to reason with it. A wyrm master who, under influence of another being hurts or kills a dragon must make amends (as decided by the CM) to prove to the dragons and himself that he was innocent. A wyrm master who is forced to kill a rogue dragon must as soon as possible cleanse himself of sin for 3 days. This rite includes hot steam baths, fasting, discussing the event with another wyrm master and prayers to Alfheim-Rigel. Any violation of these taboos results in the loss of all his abilities, and receives a negative reaction equal to his previous bonus until he atones for the act.

