Frightful Presence (Sp): Emulating the dragons he adores, at 5th level a wyrm master can unsettle foes with his mere presence. This ability takes effect automatically whenever he attacks, charges, or makes a successful Intimidate check against an opponent. Creatures within a radius of 5 ft./wyrm master level are subject to the effect if they have fewer hit dice than the wyrm master's class levels. A potentially affected creature that succeeds on a Will save (DC 10 + 1/2 wyrm masters levels + his Cha modifier) remains immune to that wyrm master's frightful presence for 24 hours. On a failure, creatures with 4 or less hit dice become panicked for 4d6 rounds and those with 5 or more hit dice become shaken for 4d6 rounds. Wyrm masters ignore the frightful presence of dragons.
